      "based_on_sources": [
        "cde_spedps",
        "cde_enrollment",
        "ca_dashboard",
        "ocr",
        "oah",
        "district_web"
      ],
      "value": "In this district about 22% of autistic students are in a general-education classroom for most of the day, and about 0.9% are in a fully separate setting. Across all students with disabilities \u2014 a broader group that includes autism along with many other categories \u2014 54% are in general-education classrooms most of the day. On 2024\u201325 state tests, students with disabilities scored about 88 points below standard in English and 112 points below in math, while students overall were 8 and 16 points below. Students with disabilities were chronically absent at about 18% (compared with 11% for all students) and suspended at about 4% (compared with 2% for all students)."
    }
